Blocks.childText: KATY DID! KATY DID N'T! FIRST SEMI-CHORUS. SECOND SEMI-CHORUS. Yes, she did, Ka - ty did, Ka - ty did - n't! Ka - ty did - n't! of 1ST SEM. 2D SEM. FULL CHORUS. Ka - ty did! Ka ty did-n't! Ka - ty did, she did! she did-n't! GENTLY LAY HER LOW. A. J. SHOWALTER. 3 4 It 1. Gen - tly, gen - tly lay her low, Soft - ly, soft - ly press the sod; 2. Plant the ros - es on her tomb, Let them bud and blossom there; 3. O'er her form the wil-lows weep, Thro' the boughs the breez-es sigh : 4. Hush ! sweet mu - sic fills the air, Sum - mer birds are sing-ing clear; 5. Gen - tly, gen - tly come a - way, Soft - ly, soft - ly press the sod; 4 ( Si - lent from the churchyard go; She's with God, She's with God. Fair are they, and in her bloom, She was fair, She was fair. And the pine groves mur - mur deep, Sound-ing nigh, Sound-ing nigh. War-blers, vain - ly chant ye there, She'll not hear, She'll not hear. Weep not as ye homeward stray, She's with God, She's with God. 41
